on that many SS men were looking forward to exacting revenge on the Americans.ï¼‰<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>ä½ ä»¬å°±è¿™æ ·äº’ç›¸å¼•ç”¨ï¼ŸOK~å¯¹åœ°æ‘Šç•Œè¦æ±‚ä¸èƒ½å¤ªé«˜~ ä½†æ˜¯è¿™ç§è‡ªå¸¦maybeçš„å‡è®¾ä¹Ÿå¯ä»¥å½“æ³¨é‡Šå—ï¼Ÿï¼Ÿï¼Ÿå¤ªä¸è´Ÿè´£äº†å§ï¼<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>è¿˜æœ‰è²Œä¼¼ä»–ç¡®å®é‡‡è®¿åˆ°å¾ˆå¤šäººï¼Œä½†åªè¦ä¸€è¨€ä¸åˆï¼ˆæˆ–è€…ç”Ÿå‰æ²¡é…åˆè®²ä½ æ´¾åè¯ï¼‰å‡ºç°åœ¨æ³¨é‡Šé‡Œå°±ä¼šæ˜¯è¿™æ ·çš„å½¢è±¡â€”â€”<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>SS-GruppenfÃ¼hrer Hermann PrieÃŸ (05/24/1901-02/02/1985) joined the NSDAP No. 1.472.296 as a &quot;March violet&quot; (SS No. 113.258) in March 1933. PrieÃŸ fought as a seventeen-year-old volunteer with the Free Corps in the Baltic area. Highly praised by Theodor Eicke as &quot;unusually reliable&quot; and &quot;unspoiled,&quot; PrieÃŸ led the SS Totenkopf Division, and won the Swords to the Knight's Cross. Seen as a commander of &quot;iron will and inner hardness,&quot; at the same time, it was suggested, that he needed an intelligent assistant! By October 24, 1944, he became Commander 1 SS Panzer Corps. Sentenced in the Malmedy Trial, PrieÃŸ was released from the Landsberg War Criminal prison by 1954. For more on PrieÃŸ, see also Sydnor: &quot;Soldaten des lodes&quot; and Weingartner: &quot;Crossroads,&quot; p. 32.<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>å“ˆå“ˆå“ˆå“ˆ Kummè¿™ä¸ªçœŸç¬‘æ­»æˆ‘äº†XDDD<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>Communication Otto Kumm to the author February 1993. SS-BrigadefÃ¼hrer Otto Kumm (10/01/1909-02/23/2004) stayed in close contact with Peiper after the war. and worked hard with the HIAG to paint a &quot;glorious&quot; pure soldier image of the Waffen-SS. Kumm. the last commander of the Leibstandarte, joined the SS in 1931 (SSNo. 18.727, NSDAP No. 421.230), and remained a convinced Nazi to his death.<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>å—¯ï¼ŒOtto Kummæ˜¯ä¸€ä¸ªåœ¨æˆ˜åä¸æ´¾æ™®ä¿æŒå¯†åˆ‡è”ç³»ï¼Œå¹¶ä¸HIAGåŠªåŠ›è¥é€ ä¸€ä¸ªâ€œå…‰è£â€çš„çº¯ç²¹çš„æ­¦è£…å…šå«å†›å†›äººå½¢è±¡çš„æ­»NZã€‚å—¯ã€‚<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>Interview with Rudolf v. Ribbentrop on 03/27/1993. Also a report from v. Ribbentrop in Lehmann: &quot;Vol. â…¢&quot; p. 200. For a different image of Peiper see ie the statements from Albert Frey to Charles Whiting. Only few veterans openly critiqued the life-disdaining leadership style of some SS commanders in the I. SS Panzer Corps in interviews with the author, most remaining anonymous. <div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>SS-Hauplsturmfuhrer Rudolf von Ribbentrop (05/11/1921), son of the German Foreign Minister, volunteered lor the SS (No. 4(X). 121) by 1939. Having been with the SS Kampfgruppe Nord in Salla in 1941, he came to the Tank regiment of the Leibstandarte by 1942. Ribbentrop was transferred to the 12th SS Panzer Division &quot;Hitlerjugend,&quot; and became commander of a scrambled Panzer Battalion there in 1945. After the war, he made his career with a well known German bank corporation. He stayed in close contact with his former comrades, and contributed to division chronicles with reports.<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>è²Œä¼¼å¤§å…¬å­ä¹Ÿæ²¡è¯´å•¥ï¼Œä¸è€æˆ˜å‹ä¿æŒè”ç³»ååŠ©å†™å¸ˆæˆ˜å²J.Wä¹Ÿä¸æ»¡æ„ï¼Ÿ<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>å™¢ï¼ŒJ.Wæ»¡æ„çš„å—è®¿è€…æ˜¯è¿™æ ·çš„ï¼š<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>Interview with Herbert Walther on 05/25/1994. SS-UntersturmfÃ¼hrer Herbert Waither (04/23/1922-02/05/2003) fought with the SS divisions &quot;Leibstandarte&quot; and &quot;Hitlerjugend.&quot; Waller was an extremely popular oddball, loved social gatherings with his old SS comrades, but hated the worshipping of former SS commanders, especially Max WÃ¼nsche and Joachim Peiper, as he made them directly responsible tor the death of numerous men due to their style of command. Walther worked with the Federal Archive in Koblenz after the war, and published several SS photo books. See ie Walther, Herbert: The Waffen-SS. Schiffer Publishing. Atglen 1989<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div> â€¦â€¦especially Max WÃ¼nsche and Joachim Peiperï¼ˆè¯´é»‘éå¾·ä¸‰çš„J.Wå”¯ç‹¬èµèµæ¸©èˆçš„ï¼Œä½ ä»¬YYçš„å¼€å¿ƒå°±å¥½23333<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>P.S. ä¸æ­¢107é¡µã€‚<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>å¯¹J.Wçš„åæ§½æš‚æ—¶åˆ°æ­¤ä¸ºæ­¢å§ã€‚æˆ‘è¿˜æœ‰å¥½å¤šä¹¦è¦çœ‹å‘¢~<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>
